<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idce2061fd-7553-11f1-8811-da7bbbed8cd8" identifier="/us/usc/t47/s1412"><num value="1412">§ 1412.</num><heading> Flexible use of narrowband spectrum</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Commission may allow the narrowband spectrum to be used in a flexible manner, including usage for public safety broadband communications, subject to such technical and interference protection measures as the Commission may require.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idce2061fe-7553-11f1-8811-da7bbbed8cd8">(<ref href="/us/pl/112/96/tVI/s6102">Pub. L. 112–96, title VI, § 6102</ref>, <date date="2012-02-22">Feb. 22, 2012</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/126/205">126 Stat. 205</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
